  </dd>
  
  <hr /><a name="bendwavy"></a>
  <dt style="font-weight: bold">BEND WAVY</dt>
  <dd>In heraldry see &lsquo;<a href="#bend">bend</a>&rsquo; (also &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dv-w.html#wavy">wavy</a>&rsquo;). 
  <p>
  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d2400.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d2400.gif" alt="Lenteg�, Spain" border="0" height="107" width="160" /></a> 
  <em><br>Flag of Lenteg�, Spain (Klaus-Michael Schneider)</em>
  </dd>

  <hr /><a name="bendlet"></a>
  <dt style="font-weight: bold">BENDLET and BENDLET SINISTER</dt>
  <dd>The heraldic term for a diminutive of bend and bend sinister, nominally half the width of a bend 
  but often much narrower, sometimes wavy and usually (but not invariably) 
  appearing in numbers of two or more � see &lsquo;bend&rsquo; and &lsquo;bend sinister&rsquo; (also &lsquo;<a href="#bend">bend</a>&rsquo; and 
  &lsquo;<a href="#bendsinister">bend sinister</a>&rsquo; (also &lsquo;<a href="#bendletwavy">bendlet 
  wavy & bendlet sinister wavy</a>&rsquo;)
  <p>
  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d2192.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d2192.gif" alt="Grolley CH" border="0" height="108" /></a>
  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d2402a.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d2402a.gif" alt="S�dtondern DE" border="0" height="108" /></a>
  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d2402.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d2402.gif" alt="S�dtondern DE" border="0" height="108" /></a><br />
  <em>Flag of <a href="ch-fr201.html">Grolley</a>, Switzerland (fotw); Arms and Flag of 
  <a href="de-nf-07.html">S�dtondern</a>, Germany (fotw)</em>
  </dd>

  <hr/><a name="bendletwavy"></a>
  <dt style="font-weight: bold">BENDLET WAVY and BENDLET SINISTER WAVY</dt>
  <dd>In heraldry see &lsquo;<a href="#bendlet">bendlet and bendlet sinister</a>&rsquo; 
  (also &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dv-w.html#wavy">wavy</a>&rsquo;).&nbsp;
  <p>
  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d2194.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d2194.gif" alt="Breenbek DE" border="0" height="108" /></a>
