  <br /><em>Big/Greater Arms of <a href="ee-talin.html#coa">Tallinn</a>, Estonia (fotw)</em>
  </dd>
  

  <hr/><a name="billet"></a>
  <dt style="font-weight: bold">BILLET
  <dd>The heraldic term for a small rectangular charge usually (but not 
  invariably) shown upright - but see &lsquo;<a href="#billetty">billetty</a>&rsquo;.
  <p><a href="../images/v/vxt-d1702.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d1702.gif" border="0" alt="Baarle-Nassau" height="108"></a>
  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d4690.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d4690.gif" border="0" alt="billet" height="108"></a>
  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d3819.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d3819.gif" border="0" alt="Tunes" height="108"></a>
  <br /><em>Flag of <a href="nl-baarl.html">Baarle-Nassau</a>, The Netherlands (fotw);
  Flag of <a href="pt-arcca.html">Cabreiros e Albergaria da Serra</a>, Portugal (fotw);
  Flag of <a href="de-ol-ga.html">Ganderkesee</a>, Germany (fotw)</em>
  </dd>
  
  <hr/><a name="billetty"></a>
  <dt style="font-weight: bold">BILLETTY
  <dd>The heraldic term sometimes used to describe a sem&eacute; of billets &ndash; see 
  &lsquo;<a href="#billet">billet</a>&rsquo; and 
  &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dvs2.html#seme">sem&eacute;</a>&rsquo;.
